---
// Static SVG: A circle with radius r labelled.
---

<figure class="diagram">
  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100%" viewBox="0 0 400 320" aria-label="A circle with radius r labelled" role="img">

    <!-- The circle -->
    <circle cx="200" cy="150" r="120" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Centre dot -->
    <circle cx="200" cy="150" r="3" fill="#555"/>

    <!-- Radius line from centre to right -->
    <line x1="200" y1="150" x2="320" y2="150" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Radius label -->
    <text x="260" y="142" font-size="14" fill="#6366f1" text-anchor="middle" font-family="serif" font-style="italic">r</text>

    <!-- Area label with question mark -->
    <text x="200" y="300" font-size="14" fill="#333" text-anchor="middle" font-family="serif">Area = ? × <tspan font-style="italic">r</tspan><tspan font-size="10" dy="-5">2</tspan></text>

  </svg>
  <figcaption>A circle of radius r — what number do we multiply r² by to get the area?</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .diagram {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .diagram svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .diagram figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
